hh3cUserLogMIB.name: hh3cUserLogMIB
hh3cUserLogMIB.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cUserLogMIB.description: The HH3C-USERLOG-MIB contains objects to Manage configuration and Monitor running state for userlog feature.

hh3cUserlogNatVersion.name: hh3cUserlogNatVersion
hh3cUserlogNatVersion.description: NAT LOG version. Currently only version 1 is developed.

hh3cUserlogNatSyslog.name: hh3cUserlogNatSyslog
hh3cUserlogNatSyslog.description: NAT LOG format. If 1, LOG format is sysLog. If 0, LOG format is UDP packet. UDP packet is the default format, and is recommended.

hh3cUserlogNatSourceIP.name: hh3cUserlogNatSourceIP
hh3cUserlogNatSourceIP.description: The Source IP address of NAT LOG UDP packet.

hh3cUserlogNatFlowBegin.name: hh3cUserlogNatFlowBegin
hh3cUserlogNatFlowBegin.description: Log the NAT flow when it is created. If 1, this function is enabled. If 0, this function is disabled. This function will be used when real-time monitor required.

hh3cUserlogNatActiveTime.name: hh3cUserlogNatActiveTime
hh3cUserlogNatActiveTime.description: The active time for long-time existed NAT flow. Unit: minute. Range: 10 minutes ~ 120 minutes. When setting it, NAT flow can be logged after an interval of active time. This function will be used when real-time monitor required. The default value 0 means real-time monitor function is disabled.

hh3cUserlogNatSlotCfgInfoTable.name: hh3cUserlogNatSlotCfgInfoTable
hh3cUserlogNatSlotCfgInfoTable.description: A table of NAT LOG configuration information for the specified slot.

hh3cUserlogNatSlotCfgInfoEntry.name: hh3cUserlogNatSlotCfgInfoEntry
hh3cUserlogNatSlotCfgInfoEntry.description: NAT LOG Configuration Information Entry for a slot.

hh3cUserlogNatCfgSlotNumber.name: hh3cUserlogNatCfgSlotNumber
hh3cUserlogNatCfgSlotNumber.description: Slot number. Specify which slot is configured with NAT LOG.

hh3cUserlogNatEnable.name: hh3cUserlogNatEnable
hh3cUserlogNatEnable.description: The NAT LOG feature Enable status. If 1, NAT LOG is enbled. If 0, NAT LOG is disabled.

hh3cUserlogNatAclNumber.name: hh3cUserlogNatAclNumber
hh3cUserlogNatAclNumber.description: Access-list number. The value 0 means no ACL is specified. Only when NAT LOG is enabled, can ACL be configured. Only NAT flow which match the ACL will be logged.

hh3cUserlogNatHostAddress.name: hh3cUserlogNatHostAddress
hh3cUserlogNatHostAddress.description: The IP address of NAT LOG server.

hh3cUserlogNatUdpPort.name: hh3cUserlogNatUdpPort
hh3cUserlogNatUdpPort.description: The UDP Port Number of NAT LOG UDP packet.

hh3cUserlogNatSlotRunInfoTable.name: hh3cUserlogNatSlotRunInfoTable
hh3cUserlogNatSlotRunInfoTable.description: A table of NAT LOG running information for the specified slot.

hh3cUserlogNatSlotRunInfoEntry.name: hh3cUserlogNatSlotRunInfoEntry
hh3cUserlogNatSlotRunInfoEntry.description: NAT LOG Running Information Entry for a slot.

hh3cUserlogNatRunSlotNumber.name: hh3cUserlogNatRunSlotNumber
hh3cUserlogNatRunSlotNumber.description: Slot number. Specify on which slot the NAT LOG statistics displayed.

hh3cUserlogNatTotalEntries.name: hh3cUserlogNatTotalEntries
hh3cUserlogNatTotalEntries.description: The total number of NAT flow entries which are logged.

hh3cUserlogNatTotalPackets.name: hh3cUserlogNatTotalPackets
hh3cUserlogNatTotalPackets.description: The total number of NAT LOG UDP packets generated by the router.

hh3cUserlogNatFailedEntries.name: hh3cUserlogNatFailedEntries
hh3cUserlogNatFailedEntries.description: The total number of NAT flow entries failed in outputting.

hh3cUserlogNatFailedPackets.name: hh3cUserlogNatFailedPackets
hh3cUserlogNatFailedPackets.description: The total number of NAT LOG UDP packets failed in outputting.

hh3cUserlogNatClearRunStat.name: hh3cUserlogNatClearRunStat
hh3cUserlogNatClearRunStat.description: Clear the running statistics for NAT LOG. Write-only. If 1, the running statistics for NAT LOG is resetted. Other value is invalid.
